The paper deals with a matrix operation that has applications in signal processing, graph theory, quantum computing, and deep learning. This suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories, including Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper's focus on fast linear transforms and the Johnson-Lindenstrauss projection further supports these sub-categories.
